To modify your JAVA_HOME when not an Administrator:

To display your current JAVA_HOME:
echo $JAVA_HOME

To change it to jdk1.8.0_221 for a given GitBash session:
export JAVA_HOME='C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_221'
export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH

To change it globally:
In the loupe icon (next to Start), type Control Panel.
In the Control Panel, select User Accounts.
In the User Accounts, select “Change my environment variables”.


***


To give Admin rights to user johndoe:
Being logged in as johndoe, launch a command prompt as Administrator.
Type compmgmt.msc
In the popup window, expand local users and groups.
Double-click groups.
Type johndoe
Search for it, validate by entering credentials for johndoe.
Click Apply, OK & Exit.
